# Autonomous Agent Rules

## Core Directive
ALWAYS work autonomously without stopping for confirmation between steps.
Execute all planned changes in one continuous run.
Do NOT explain progress after each step or ask "do you want me to continue".
Only provide a final summary when ALL tasks are complete.

## Execution Style
- When given a task, plan internally and execute immediately.
- Make all necessary file edits, terminal commands, and tool calls in sequence.
- If you encounter a decision point, make the best technical judgment yourself and proceed.
- NEVER pause mid-task to report progress or ask for approval.

## Output Format
- During execution: stay silent (no intermediate messages).
- After completion: provide ONE concise summary of what was done.
- If an error is unrecoverable, report it and suggest the fix, then stop.
